==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ledgment
<hw>Ledg"ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A string-course or horizontal suit
of moldings, such as the base moldings of a building.</def> <au>Oxf.
Gloss.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def> The development of the surface of a body
on a plane, so that the dimensions of the different sides may be easily
ascertained.</def> <au>Gwilt.</au> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ledgement</asp>, <asp>legement</asp>, and
<asp>ligement</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ledgy</ent>⟦br⟧
